Episodes.Title: Pilot
Episodes.Plot: Liz Lemon is called upstairs to meet the new network exec, Jack Donaghy, who instructs her to hire movie star Tracy Jordan to draw a young male audience to 'The Girlie Show'.
Episodes.GuestStars: Rachel Dratch, Keith Powell, Lonny Ross, Maulik Pancholy, Katrina Bowden, Tom Broecker, Teddy Coluca, Gary Cowling

Episodes.Title: The Aftermath
Episodes.Plot: Jack continues to tweak The Girlie Show so that eccentric Tracy Jordan is the star of the show. And Liz makes it all much worse when she tries to smooth things over.
Episodes.GuestStars: Keith Powell, Katrina Bowden, Lonny Ross, Teddy Coluca, Maulik Pancholy, Rachel Dratch, Sorab Wadia, Adrienne Frost, Tom Broecker, Kevin Scanlon

Episodes.Title: Blind Date
Episodes.Plot: Cupid has a new rival when Jack insists on sending Liz on a blind date with his out of town friend, Thomas.
Episodes.GuestStars: Katrina Bowden, Keith Powell, Lonny Ross, Maulik Pancholy, Teddy Coluca, Grizz Chapman, John Lutz, Kevin Kelly Brown, Stephanie March, Brett Baer

Episodes.Title: Jack the Writer
Episodes.Plot: Lines are drawn when Jack decides to sit in on the writers' room and Kenneth the page tries to deal with Tracy's difficult demands.
Episodes.GuestStars: Keith Powell, Katrina Bowden, John Lutz, Maulik Pancholy, Sharon Wilkins, James Anderson, Tom Broecker

Episodes.Title: Jack-Tor
Episodes.Plot: Jack is determined to act in a sketch on the show. Liz suspects Tracy may be illiterate.
Episodes.GuestStars: Teddy Coluca, Keith Powell, Maulik Pancholy, Lonny Ross, Katrina Bowden, Matthew Stocke, James Murtaugh

Episodes.Title: Jack Meets Dennis
Episodes.Plot: Liz reconnects with her ex-boyfriend Dennis, the last remaining pager salesman in New York. Meanwhile, Jenna and Tracy try to "enhance" their appearances for career reasons.
Episodes.GuestStars: Dean Winters, Michael Blackson, Greta Cavazzoni, Teddy Coluca, Brian Stack, Katrina Bowden, Keith Powell, Lonny Ross, Rachel Dratch, Ali Reza

Episodes.Title: Tracy Does Conan
Episodes.Plot: It's a star showdown when a dazed and confused Tracy bumps Jenna from her scheduled appearance on Late Night with Conan O'brien.
Episodes.GuestStars: Dean Winters, Conan O'Brien, Kevin Kelly Brown, Chris Parnell, Grizz Chapman, Maulik Pancholy, Rachel Dratch, Keith Powell, Katrina Bowden

Episodes.Title: The Break Up
Episodes.Plot: At the urging of everyone, Liz finally breaks up with her beeper salesman boyfriend, but the path back to "single and loving it" proves to be filled with unforeseen obstacles.
Episodes.GuestStars: Dean Winters, Rachel Dratch, Chris Hansen, Devin Richards, Maulik Pancholy, Katrina Bowden, Keith Powell, Lonny Ross, Stan Tracy, Henry Boyle

Episodes.Title: The Baby Show
Episodes.Plot: There are mommy issues on the set when Jenna tells everyone that Liz wants to get pregnant, and Jack gives her some very personal parental advice.
Episodes.GuestStars: Rachel Dratch, Chris Parnell, Katrina Bowden, John Lutz, Maulik Pancholy, Lonny Ross, Keith Powell, Jeff Richmond, Jack Hallett, Bridget Moloney

Episodes.Title: The Rural Juror
Episodes.Plot: Jenna can't wait for her new movie to open, but Liz won't tell her what she really thinks of her performance.
Episodes.GuestStars: Lonny Ross, Kevin Kelly Brown, Chris Parnell, Keith Powell, Maulik Pancholy, Rachel Dratch

Episodes.Title: The Head and the Hair
Episodes.Plot: There are some new power players around when Jack and Kenneth the page switch roles for the day and Liz finds herself clicking with a gorgeous hunk.

Episodes.Title: Black Tie
Episodes.Plot: Liz, Jack and Jenna rub elbows with the upper crust at a prince's (Paul Reubens) birthday party. But the end of the evening finds Liz lying low after Jack's ex-wife (Isabella Rossellini) shows up.

Episodes.Title: Up All Night
Episodes.Plot: Valentine's Day is much more than candy and flowers when Jack celebrates the finalization of his divorce and the writers are forced to pull an all-nighter.
Episodes.GuestStars: Mark Zimmerman, Rachel Hamilton, Isabella Rossellini

Episodes.Title: The 'C' Word
Episodes.Plot: Being the boss isn't all it's cracked up to be when Liz overhears the writers discussing her management style and Jack tries to impress CEO Don Geiss (Rip Torn) at a charity golf tournament by bringing Tracy along.
Episodes.GuestStars: Darlene J. Camille, Paul Doherty, Tamara Fay, Rachel Hamilton, Kevin Miller, Charlene Yi, Teresa Yenque, Tom Treadwell, Sam Kitchin, Justin Badger

Episodes.Title: Hard Ball
Episodes.Plot: It's negotiation time, and Jack plans to teach Liz a thing or two about how to handle Josh's new contract. Jenna makes several big publicity mistakes.
Episodes.GuestStars: David Alan Basche, Gregory Wooddell, Gregg Bello

Episodes.Title: The Source Awards
Episodes.Plot: It's lights, camera, aggravation when Liz finds herself locked in a relationship with Tracy's determined new manager and Jack forces Tracy to host The Source Awards (special guests L.L. Cool J and Wayne Brady).
Episodes.GuestStars: Lonny Ross, Kevin Brown, Chris Matthews, Tucker Carlson, Keith Powell, Gregg Bello, Gregory Wooddell, David Alan Basche, Katrina Bowden

Episodes.Title: The Fighting Irish
Episodes.Plot: Family matters move front and centre when Jack is reunited with his down-and-out brother (Nathan Lane) and Liz has a tough time making staff cutbacks.
Episodes.GuestStars: Wayne Brady, Ghostface Killah, LL Cool J

Episodes.Title: Fireworks
Episodes.Plot: Sparks are flying when Jack uses Kenneth the page to thwart an aggressive west coast NBC exec (Will Arnett) and Liz follows her crush to an AA meeting.
Episodes.GuestStars: Nathan Lane, Anna Chlumsky, Lonny Ross, Katrina Bowden, Maulik Pancholy, Brian Murray, Siobhan Fallon Hogan, Boris McGiver, Molly Shannon, Dan Bakkedahl, Chris Hoch, Alice Kremelberg, Henry Boyle, John F. Mooney

Episodes.Title: Corporate Crush
Episodes.Plot: Love is in the air, but Liz is concerned when Jack takes an overwhelming interest in her new boyfriend (Jason Sudeikis).
Episodes.GuestStars: Rip Torn, John Lutz, Maulik Pancholy

Episodes.Title: Cleveland
Episodes.Plot: There are certainly no sparks when Jack asks Liz to take his fiancee, Phoebe (Emily Mortimer), out for a ladies' lunch. But Liz finds a lot more to like when her boyfriend takes her to the great city of Cleveland.

Episodes.Title: Hiatus
Episodes.Plot: Tracy, on the run from the Black Crusaders, goes into hiding with Kenneth's cousin Jessie (Sean Hayes), and the pressure's on Liz to make the show work after Jack's mother (Elaine Stritch) arrives and Jack ends up in the hospital.
